{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Home Credit Default Risk - Exploratory Data Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "**Business Problem:** Predict which clients are likely to default on their loan payments. This analysis explores the application data to understand patterns, identify strong predictors, and prepare data for modeling.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset Overview:**\n",
    "- Training set: 307,511 clients with loan outcomes\n",
    "- Test set: 48,744 clients for prediction\n",
    "- 122 application features + supplementary transactional data\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. Setup & Data Loading"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set style and configuration\n",
    "sns.set_style('whitegrid')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (12, 6)\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load data\n",
    "data_dir = Path('C:/Users/abdul/Downloads')\n",
    "train = pd.read_csv(data_dir / 'application_train.csv')\n",
    "test = pd.read_csv(data_dir / 'application_test.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Train shape: {train.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'Test shape: {test.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'\\nFirst few rows:')\n",
    "train.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2. Target Variable Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### Is the data unbalanced?\n",
    "\n",
    "The target variable (0 = repaid, 1 = defaulted) is critical for understanding the modeling challenge. Class imbalance affects both model selection and evaluation metrics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Target distribution\n",
    "target_counts = train['TARGET'].value_counts().sort_index()\n",
    "target_pct = 100 * train['TARGET'].value_counts(normalize=True).sort_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Summary table\n",
    "summary = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Class': ['No Default (0)', 'Default (1)'],\n",
    "    'Count': [target_counts[0], target_counts[1]],\n",
    "    'Percentage': [f\"{target_pct[0]:.2f}%\", f\"{target_pct[1]:.2f}%\"]\n",
    "})\n",
    "print('TARGET VARIABLE DISTRIBUTION')\n",
    "print(summary.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Baseline accuracy\n",
    "baseline_accuracy = target_pct.max()\n",
    "imbalance_ratio = target_counts[0] / target_counts[1]\n",
    "print(f'\\n✓ Majority class baseline accuracy: {baseline_accuracy:.2f}%')\n",
    "print(f'✓ Class imbalance ratio (No Default : Default): {imbalance_ratio:.2f}:1')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualization\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bar chart\n",
    "colors = ['#2ecc71', '#e74c3c']\n",
    "ax1.bar(['No Default', 'Default'], target_counts, color=colors, alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel('Number of Clients', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Target Variable Distribution (Count)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax1.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "for i, v in enumerate(target_counts):\n",
    "    ax1.text(i, v + 5000, f'{v:,}', ha='center', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pie chart\n",
    "ax2.pie(target_counts, labels=['No Default', 'Default'], autopct='%1.1f%%', \n",
    "        colors=colors, startangle=90, textprops={'fontsize': 11, 'fontweight': 'bold'})\n",
    "ax2.set_title('Target Variable Distribution (Percentage)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\n📊 KEY INSIGHT: The dataset is HIGHLY IMBALANCED (11.7:1 ratio).')\n",
    "print('   A naive model predicting \"No Default\" for all clients would achieve 92.0% accuracy')\n",
    "print('   but would fail to identify ANY actual defaults. This requires:')\n",
    "print('   • Stratified cross-validation')\n",
    "print('   • Class weights or resampling')\n",
    "print('   • Focus on AUPRC, precision-recall, and F1-score metrics')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3. Relationship Between Target & Predictors\n",
    "\n",
    "### Which features are most predictive of default?\n",
    "\n",
    "We examine numeric features through correlation analysis and visualize the strongest predictors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate correlations with target\n",
    "numeric_cols = train.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\n",
    "numeric_cols = [c for c in numeric_cols if c not in ['TARGET', 'SK_ID_CURR']]\n",
    "\n",
    "correlations = {}\n",
    "for col in numeric_cols:\n",
    "    # Use only non-missing values\n",
    "    valid_mask = train[col].notna() & train['TARGET'].notna()\n",
    "    if valid_mask.sum() > 10:\n",
    "        corr = train.loc[valid_mask, col].corr(train.loc[valid_mask, 'TARGET'])\n",
    "        correlations[col] = corr\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create sorted dataframe\n",
    "corr_df = pd.DataFrame(list(correlations.items()), columns=['Feature', 'Correlation'])\n",
    "corr_df['Abs_Corr'] = np.abs(corr_df['Correlation'])\n",
    "corr_df = corr_df.sort_values('Abs_Corr', ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('TOP 15 NUMERIC PREDICTORS (by absolute correlation with TARGET)')\n",
    "print(corr_df.head(15)[['Feature', 'Correlation']].to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize top 4 predictors\n",
    "top_4 = corr_df.head(4)['Feature'].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\n",
    "axes = axes.flatten()\n",
    "\n",
    "for idx, col in enumerate(top_4):\n",
    "    no_default = train[train['TARGET'] == 0][col].dropna()\n",
    "    default = train[train['TARGET'] == 1][col].dropna()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    axes[idx].hist([no_default, default], bins=50, label=['No Default', 'Default'], \n",
    "                   color=['#2ecc71', '#e74c3c'], alpha=0.6, edgecolor='black')\n",
    "    axes[idx].set_title(f'{col}\\n(Correlation: {correlations[col]:.4f})', \n",
    "                        fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "    axes[idx].set_xlabel(col, fontsize=10)\n",
    "    axes[idx].set_ylabel('Frequency', fontsize=10)\n",
    "    axes[idx].legend()\n",
    "    axes[idx].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\n📊 INTERPRETATION:')\n",
    "print('   • EXT_SOURCE features show clearest separation between classes')\n",
    "print('   • Higher external credit scores → lower default risk')\n",
    "print('   • Age and income have weaker but still meaningful associations')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 4. Missing Data Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is the scope of missing data? What strategy should we use?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Missing data summary\n",
    "missing_train = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Column': train.columns,\n",
    "    'Missing_Count': train.isnull().sum(),\n",
    "    'Missing_Pct': 100 * train.isnull().sum() / len(train),\n",
    "    'Data_Type': train.dtypes\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "missing_train = missing_train[missing_train['Missing_Pct'] > 0].sort_values('Missing_Pct', ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Columns with ANY missing data: {len(missing_train)}')\n",
    "print('\\nTOP 20 COLUMNS BY MISSING PERCENTAGE:')\n",
    "print(missing_train.head(20)[['Column', 'Missing_Pct', 'Missing_Count']].to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# High missing threshold\n",
    "high_missing = missing_train[missing_train['Missing_Pct'] > 70]\n",
    "print(f'\\n⚠️ Columns with >70% missing: {len(high_missing)}')\n",
    "if len(high_missing) > 0:\n",
    "    print(high_missing[['Column', 'Missing_Pct']].to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualization of missing data\n",
    "missing_pct_vals = missing_train.head(20)['Missing_Pct'].values\n",
    "missing_cols = missing_train.head(20)['Column'].values\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "colors_missing = ['#e74c3c' if x > 70 else '#f39c12' if x > 50 else '#3498db' for x in missing_pct_vals]\n",
    "ax.barh(range(len(missing_pct_vals)), missing_pct_vals, color=colors_missing, edgecolor='black')\n",
    "ax.set_yticks(range(len(missing_cols)))\n",
    "ax.set_yticklabels(missing_cols, fontsize=9)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Missing Percentage (%)', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Top 20 Columns by Missing Data', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.axvline(x=50, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label='50% threshold')\n",
    "ax.axvline(x=70, color='darkred', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label='70% threshold')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(axis='x', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('\\n' + '='*70)\n",
    "print('PROPOSED MISSING DATA HANDLING STRATEGY')\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "print('''\n",
    "1. REMOVE columns with >70% missing data\n",
    "   Rationale: Too sparse to reliably impute or model\n",
    "   Action: Drop these features entirely\n",
    "   \n",
    "2. For NUMERIC columns (5-70% missing):\n",
    "   • Missing <20%: Impute with MEDIAN (robust to outliers)\n",
    "   • Missing 20-70%: Impute with MEDIAN + CREATE missing indicator flag\n",
    "   Rationale: Missing indicator preserves information about missingness patterns\n",
    "   \n",
    "3. For CATEGORICAL columns (any % missing):\n",
    "   • Create new category 'Unknown' or use mode\n",
    "   • Create missing indicator for informative missingness\n",
    "   \n",
    "4. ROWS: Do NOT remove rows with missing values\n",
    "   Rationale: Only 2 columns missing in few rows; better to impute\n",
    "   Exception: Would remove if single column had >95% missing in one row\n",
    "''')\n",
    "print('='*70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 5. Data Quality Issues\n",
    "\n",
    "### Are there problems in the data? Outliers? Sentinel values? Near-zero variance?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check for duplicates\n",
    "print('DATA QUALITY CHECKS')\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "print(f'Duplicate rows: {train.duplicated().sum()}')\n",
    "print(f'Duplicate SK_ID_CURR: {train[\"SK_ID_CURR\"].duplicated().sum()}')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Identify sentinel values and suspicious patterns\n",
    "print('SUSPICIOUS VALUES (potential sentinel values or errors):')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# DAYS_EMPLOYED: large sentinel value (365243)\n",
    "days_employed_sentinel = (train['DAYS_EMPLOYED'] == 365243).sum()\n",
    "print(f'• DAYS_EMPLOYED = 365243 (likely unemployed/unknown): {days_employed_sentinel:,} ({100*days_employed_sentinel/len(train):.1f}%)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# AMT_INCOME_TOTAL: extreme outliers\n",
    "income_99th = train['AMT_INCOME_TOTAL'].quantile(0.99)\n",
    "extreme_income = (train['AMT_INCOME_TOTAL'] > income_99th).sum()\n",
    "print(f'• AMT_INCOME_TOTAL extreme values (>99th percentile): {extreme_income:,}')\n",
    "print(f'  99th percentile: ${income_99th:,.0f}')\n",
    "print(f'  Max value: ${train[\"AMT_INCOME_TOTAL\"].max():,.0f}')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# DAYS_BIRTH and DAYS_EMPLOYED: negative values (expected, measured in days before application)\n",
    "print(f'• DAYS_BIRTH (all negative, expected): Min={train[\"DAYS_BIRTH\"].min()}, Max={train[\"DAYS_BIRTH\"].max()}')\n",
    "print(f'• DAYS_EMPLOYED (mostly negative, expected): Min={train[\"DAYS_EMPLOYED\"].min()}, Max={train[\"DAYS_EMPLOYED\"].max()}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Near-zero variance check\n",
    "print('\\nNEAR-ZERO VARIANCE COLUMNS (unsuitable for modeling):')\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "\n",
    "variance_threshold = 0.05  # 5% or less of unique non-missing values\n",
    "low_variance_cols = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for col in train.columns:\n",
    "    if train[col].dtype == 'object':  # Categorical\n",
    "        n_unique = train[col].nunique()\n",
    "        n_total = train[col].notna().sum()\n",
    "        unique_pct = n_unique / n_total * 100\n",
    "    else:  # Numeric\n",
    "        n_unique = train[col].nunique()\n",
    "        unique_pct = n_unique / len(train) * 100\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if unique_pct <= variance_threshold:\n",
    "        low_variance_cols.append({\n",
    "            'Column': col,\n",
    "            'Unique_Values': n_unique,\n",
    "            'Unique_Pct': unique_pct,\n",
    "            'Type': train[col].dtype\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "if low_variance_cols:\n",
    "    low_var_df = pd.DataFrame(low_variance_cols).sort_values('Unique_Pct')\n",
    "    print(low_var_df.to_string(index=False))\nelse:\n",
    "    print('None found - all columns have sufficient variance')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 6. Data Transformation Requirements\n",
    "\n",
    "### Will data need to be transformed for modeling?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code">
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('DATA TRANSFORMATION CONSIDERATIONS')\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "print('''\n",
    "MODEL TYPE IMPLICATIONS:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. TREE-BASED MODELS (Random Forest, XGBoost, LightGBM)\n",
    "   ✓ Handle categorical variables natively (no encoding needed)\n",
    "   ✓ Handle missing values well\n",
    "   ✓ Robust to outliers\n",
    "   ✓ NO scaling needed\n",
    "   ✗ May require one-hot encoding if using sklearn\n",
    "   Action: Minimal transformation; mainly imputation & encoding\n",
    "   \n",
    "2. LINEAR MODELS (Logistic Regression)\n",
    "   ✓ Interpretable coefficients\n",
    "   ✗ Require ALL numeric inputs\n",
    "   ✗ Sensitive to feature scaling\n",
    "   ✗ Sensitive to outliers\n",
    "   ✗ Cannot handle missing values\n",
    "   Action: One-hot encode categorical, normalize numeric, handle outliers\n",
    "   \n",
    "3. NEURAL NETWORKS\n",
    "   ✗ Require numeric inputs only\n",
    "   ✗ Very sensitive to scaling\n",
    "   ✓ Handle missing values with imputation\n",
    "   Action: One-hot encode all categoricals, standardize scale, impute\n",
    "\n",
    "RECOMMENDED TRANSFORMATIONS (for maximum flexibility):\n",
    "□ Impute missing numeric values (median)\n",
    "□ Create missing indicator flags for high-missingness columns\n",
    "□ Handle sentinel values (e.g., DAYS_EMPLOYED = 365243)\n",
    "□ One-hot encode categorical variables\n",
    "□ Standardize numeric features for distance-based/linear models\n",
    "□ Consider log transforms for heavily right-skewed features\n",
    "□ Treat extreme outliers carefully (domain-informed decisions)\n",
    "''')\n",
    "print('='*70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 7. Joining Transactional Data\n",
    "\n",
    "### Loading and aggregating supplementary datasets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load supplementary datasets\n",
    "bureau = pd.read_csv(data_dir / 'bureau.csv')\n",
    "bureau_balance = pd.read_csv(data_dir / 'bureau_balance.csv')\n",
    "previous_app = pd.read_csv(data_dir / 'previous_application.csv')\n",
    "credit_card = pd.read_csv(data_dir / 'credit_card_balance.csv')\n",
    "installments = pd.read_csv(data_dir / 'installments_payments.csv')\n",
    "pos_cash = pd.read_csv(data_dir / 'POS_CASH_balance.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('SUPPLEMENTARY DATASETS LOADED')\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "print(f'Bureau credits: {bureau.shape[0]:,} records')\n",
    "print(f'Bureau balance: {bureau_balance.shape[0]:,} records')\n",
    "print(f'Previous applications: {previous_app.shape[0]:,} records')\n",
    "print(f'Credit card balance: {credit_card.shape[0]:,} records')\n",
    "print(f'Installment payments: {installments.shape[0]:,} records')\n",
    "print(f'POS cash balance: {pos_cash.shape[0]:,} records')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Coverage check\n",
    "bureau_clients = bureau['SK_ID_CURR'].nunique()\n",
    "train_clients = train['SK_ID_CURR'].nunique()\n",
    "print(f'Data coverage:')\n",
    "print(f'  Bureau: {bureau_clients:,} / {train_clients:,} clients ({100*bureau_clients/train_clients:.1f}%)')\n",
    "print(f'  Previous apps: {previous_app[\"SK_ID_CURR\"].nunique():,} / {train_clients:,} ({100*previous_app[\"SK_ID_CURR\"].nunique()/train_clients:.1f}%)')\n",
    "print(f'  Credit card: {credit_card[\"SK_ID_CURR\"].nunique():,} / {train_clients:,} ({100*credit_card[\"SK_ID_CURR\"].nunique()/train_clients:.1f}%)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Aggregate bureau data to client level\n",
    "bureau_agg = bureau.groupby('SK_ID_CURR').agg({\n",
    "    'CREDIT_TYPE': 'nunique',  # Number of different credit types\n",
    "    'AMT_CREDIT_SUM': ['sum', 'mean', 'max'],\n",
    "    'AMT_CREDIT_SUM_DEBT': ['sum', 'mean', 'max'],\n",
    "    'DAYS_CREDIT': ['min', 'max', 'mean'],  # Most/least recent credit\n",
    "    'CNT_CREDIT_PROLONG': 'sum',  # Total credit prolongations\n",
    "    'CREDIT_DAY_OVERDUE': ['max', 'mean']\n",
    "}).reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Flatten column names\n",
    "bureau_agg.columns = ['_'.join(col).strip('_') if col[1] else col[0] for col in bureau_agg.columns.values]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('AGGREGATED BUREAU FEATURES')\n",
    "print(f'Shape: {bureau_agg.shape}')\n",
    "print(bureau_agg.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Aggregate previous applications\n",
    "prev_agg = previous_app.groupby('SK_ID_CURR').agg({\n",
    "    'SK_ID_PREV': 'nunique',  # Number of previous applications\n",
    "    'AMT_APPLICATION': ['sum', 'mean', 'max'],\n",
    "    'NAME_CONTRACT_TYPE': lambda x: (x == 'Revolving loans').sum(),  # Count revolving loans\n",
    "    'NAME_CONTRACT_STATUS': lambda x: (x == 'Refused').sum()  # Count refused applications\n",
    "}).reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "prev_agg.columns = ['SK_ID_CURR', 'n_previous_apps', 'prev_amt_sum', 'prev_amt_mean', \n",
    "                     'prev_amt_max', 'n_revolving_loans', 'n_refused_apps']\n",
    "\n",
    "print('AGGREGATED PREVIOUS APPLICATION FEATURES')\n",
    "print(f'Shape: {prev_agg.shape}')\n",
    "print(prev_agg.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Aggregate credit card data\n",
    "credit_agg = credit_card.groupby('SK_ID_CURR').agg({\n",
    "    'AMT_BALANCE': ['mean', 'max', 'sum'],\n",
    "    'AMT_CREDIT_LIMIT_ACTUAL': 'mean',\n",
    "    'MONTHS_BALANCE': 'nunique'  # Number of months with activity\n",
    "}).reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "credit_agg.columns = ['SK_ID_CURR', 'cc_balance_mean', 'cc_balance_max', 'cc_balance_sum',\n",
    "                      'cc_limit_mean', 'cc_months_active']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate credit utilization\n",
    "credit_agg['cc_utilization'] = credit_agg['cc_balance_mean'] / (credit_agg['cc_limit_mean'] + 1e-6)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('AGGREGATED CREDIT CARD FEATURES')\n",
    "print(f'Shape: {credit_agg.shape}')\n",
    "print(credit_agg.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
